header.gameNote: TOP OF THE WORLD CLASSIC AT FAIRBANKS AK

article.headline: Utah State 77, Centenary 71
article.story: FAIRBANKS, Alaska (AP) -- Jaycee Carroll scored 27 points and Utah State defeated Centenary 77-71 Friday in the opening round of the BP Top of the World Classic. Durrall Peterson opened the game with two 3-pointers and Carroll scored 17 as the Aggies (1-1) took a 46-26 lead into intermission. Centenary (1-2), which shot 15-for-16 from the free thrown line, fought back with an 18-4 run, including seven points by Bryan Bauman, to cut the lead to 50-44 with 10 minutes left to play. The Aggies responded with a 10-4 spurt, capped by a 3-pointer by Carroll with 6:18 remaining. Centenary hit three 3-pointers in the last minute for the final margin. Utah State dominated the boards 29-16 with Michael Earl pulling down eight. Chase Adams had 17 points and Bauman had 14 for the Gents. Peterson finished with 11 points for the Aggies.
